<h1>All Campgrounds</h1>
<div class="mb-4 mt-4">
    <a href="/campgrounds/new" class="btn btn-info"> Add Campground </a>
</div>
<ol>
    <% for (let cg of campgrounds) {%>
    <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <!-- 4/12 taken horizontally -->
                <img src="<%=cg.images[0].url %>" class="img-fluid" alt="" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-8">
                <!-- remaining 8/12 horizontally -->
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title"><%=cg.title %></h5>
                    <p class="card-text">
                        <small class="text-secondary"><%=cg.location %></small>
                    </p>
                    <p class="card-text"><%=cg.description %></p>
                    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="campgrounds/<%=cg._id %>"
                        >Explore <%=cg.title %></a
                    >
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <%}%>
</ol>

<!-- note : Explanations -->

<!-- 
? Breakdown of col-md-4
    * col:
    - Represents a single column within a row in the grid system.
    - The number of columns (e.g., 4 in col-md-4) specifies the portion of the grid the column will occupy.
    * md:
    - Stands for medium breakpoint (768px and up).
    - The column settings specified (4) will apply when the screen size is medium or larger (â‰¥768px).
    * 4:
    -Indicates the column will take up 4 out of 12 columns in the Bootstrap grid.
    -Bootstrap's grid system divides the page into a 12-column layout, so 4 columns mean the div will occupy one-third of the row's width.
-->

